<TITLE> Ramadan will be free of food crisis: CA </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Aug 14 (bdnews24.com)  There would be no food crisis in Ramadan since the government has replenished food stocks with imports, chief adviser Fakhruddin Ahmed was quoted as saying on Thursday. The interim government head briefed president Iajuddin Ahmed at a meeting at Bangabhaban, about the steps his administration has taken, president's press secretary Abdul Awal Hawlader told reporters. The government decided to start Open Market Sale of rice on August 20 to keep food supplies normal and rein in prices of commodities during the month, he told the president. Besides, fair price shops would be opened with the help of BDR, Ansar, Fakhruddin said. The chief adviser, who went to Bangabhaban around 1:45pm, also talked with the president about the 15th SAARC summit in Colombo. Secretary at President's office Sirajul Islam, military secretary to the President Major General Ruhul Amin, secretary at the Chief Adviser's Office Kazi Md Aminul Islam and CA's press secretary Syed Fahim Munaim were present at the meeting. bdnews24
